{{Wireless embedded system |brand=EnGenius |model=ESR9850 |upc=655216004214 |asin=B002TY785A |fcc_date=07/28/2009 |manuf_country=Taiwan |is_manuf=No |manuf=Senao |type=wireless router |fcc_id=U2M-SR9850 |ic_id=3616C-SR985010 |pwr_v=12 |pwr_amp=1 |pwr_conn=barrel |cpu1_brand=Ralink |cpu1_model=RT3052 |cpu1_cspeed=384 |fla1=4 |fla1_brand=Macronix |fla1_model=MX29LV320ETTI-70G |ram1=32 |ram1_brand=Zentel |ram1_model=A3V28S40FTP-G6 |ram1_num=2 |serial=4-pad header |wi1_chip1_brand=Ralink |wi1_chip1_model=RT3052 |wi1_802dot11_protocols=bgn |wi1_ant_conn=RP-SMA |wi1_txchains=2 |wi1_rxchains=2 |wi1_sstreams=2 |eth_cpu=true |sw_brand=Realtek |sw_model=RTL8366RB |lan_speed=1G |lan_ports=4 |wan_ports=1 |802dot11_protocols=bgn |default_ssid=EnGeniusXXXXXX, |default_ssid_regex=^Engenius$ |default_ip=192.168.0.1 |default_user=admin |default_pass=admin |oui=00:02:6F |oui_eth=00:02:6F |default_ch= }} The FCC test report lists the Sitecom WL-351 and Rosewill RNX-N400 as additional models. The [http://www.dd-wrt.com/wiki/index.php/Supported_Devices DD-WRT wiki] additionally lists the Sitecom WL-368. This probably also includes the Sitecom WLR-4000 [http://www.dd-wrt.com/phpBB2/viewtopic.php?t=153420].
The DD-WRT wiki cites the device as having 4MB Flash and 32MB RAM and the current status as a WiP.
"7016A0305000 Ver:1.00" is silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos.
